                  <decoDesc>
                     <summary>Seven tinted drawings of the planets in Hindu mythology with captions
                        in Persian, separately executed by an unidentifed artist on horizontal
                        strips of paper, inserted into the gutter margins adjacent to blank spaces
                        intended for them. Therefore, to view them properly, place the a side of the
                        insert against the a side of the adjacent folio, etc:</summary>
                     <decoNote type="illustration"><list>
                           <item><locus from="8b" to="8b">Insert 1b, viewed against folio
                              8b</locus>: Saturn.</item>
                           <item><locus from="9a" to="9a">Insert 1a, viewed against folio
                              9a</locus>: Jupiter.</item>
                           <item>Folio <locus from="9b" to="9b">9b</locus>: Mars.</item>
                           <item>Folio <locus from="10a" to="10a">10a</locus>: Sun.</item>
                           <item>Folio <locus from="10b" to="10b">10b</locus>: Venus.</item>
                           <item>Folio <locus from="11a" to="11a">11a</locus>: Mercury.</item>
                           <item>Folio <locus from="11b" to="11b">11b</locus>: Moon.</item>
                        </list>
                     </decoNote>
